From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [G10] preserve_thinking kwarg (default OFF) — keep historical tool-call reasoning

Targets: templates/gemma4/patched/{26B-A4B-it,31B-it,E2B-it,E4B-it}.jinja (state after G7 + G9 applied)

Failure mode. Gemma 4 drops prior-turn reasoning from history: the dedicated
`reasoning` / `reasoning_content` field is rendered as a `<|channel>thought`
block only for the CURRENT-turn region — the guard is
`loop.index0 > ns_turn.last_user_idx and message.get('tool_calls')`. So a
HISTORICAL tool-call turn's reasoning is never re-emitted. In multi-step
agentic loops the model loses the trace of how it chose arguments last time
and, after 2-3 turns, later tool calls collapse to `arguments: {}` even though
the prior reasoning had identified the parameters. Symptom documented for both
Qwen3.6 (earendil-works/pi#3325, the Q3.6-1 analog) and Gemma 4 (r/LocalLLaMA
12B tool-calling threads).

Fix. Add a `preserve_thinking` kwarg. When set true, relax the
current-region-only guard so historical tool-call reasoning is rendered too:
```jinja
{%- if thinking_text and ((preserve_thinking is defined and preserve_thinking) or loop.index0 > ns_turn.last_user_idx) and message.get('tool_calls') -%}
```

Default OFF (deliberate). When `preserve_thinking` is unset/false the render is
**byte-identical** to upstream — verified across the no-kwarg and
`preserve_thinking=false` paths. We do NOT default it on (unlike Qwen3.6's
Q3.6-1, where the publisher's model card recommends it): Google's reasoning-
preservation change is still an UNMERGED PR (HF disc #118) and the community
stance was contested, so a derived patch must not presume Google's intent. The
kwarg is an opt-in escape hatch for agentic users hitting the collapse bug, and
it lays the plumbing for a future default-flip (a "G10b", à la Q3.6-1→Q3.6-2)
once #118 lands or the model card confirms the stance.

Scope. Gates only the reasoning-FIELD render (mechanism A). It deliberately
leaves `strip_thinking()` (which removes `<|channel>thought` embedded in model
CONTENT) unchanged — the documented bug is the OpenAI-harness flow where
reasoning arrives in the `reasoning_content` field, not embedded in content.
Also preserves the template's existing tool-call scoping (`and tool_calls`):
non-tool assistant turns still drop reasoning, matching upstream design.

KV-cache note. preserve_thinking IMPROVES prefix symmetry: a tool-call turn
that rendered WITH thinking while current would, without this patch, re-render
WITHOUT thinking once it becomes history (a cache-busting asymmetry). With the
kwarg on, history matches the original generation.

Stacks on G7 + G9. Diff is against the G7+G9-applied state. Applied identically
to all four patched sizes; the hunk below for 26B-A4B-it is representative.

--- a/templates/gemma4/patched/26B-A4B-it.jinja
+++ b/templates/gemma4/patched/26B-A4B-it.jinja
@@ -245,7 +245,8 @@
 
     {#- Render reasoning/reasoning_content as thinking channel -#}
     {%- set thinking_text = message.get('reasoning') or message.get('reasoning_content') -%}
-    {%- if thinking_text and loop.index0 > ns_turn.last_user_idx and message.get('tool_calls') -%}
+    {#- G10: preserve_thinking (default OFF) — when set, render historical tool-call reasoning too (not just the current-turn region), curing the agentic arguments-collapse where dropped prior reasoning makes later tool calls emit `arguments: {}`. Byte-identical to upstream when the kwarg is unset. Derived; upstream analog: Google PR HF disc #118 (unmerged). -#}
+    {%- if thinking_text and ((preserve_thinking is defined and preserve_thinking) or loop.index0 > ns_turn.last_user_idx) and message.get('tool_calls') -%}
         {{- '<|channel>thought\n' + thinking_text + '\n<channel|>' -}}
     {%- endif -%}
 
